OL,3,CRoyal Opera conductor replaces sick
OL,4,Ctenor during live show
OL,6,FA conductor, dressed in a jumper and
OL,7,Fchinos, was forced to sing the lead
OL,8,Frole from the wings during a
OL,9,Fperformance at the Royal Opera House
OL,10,Fon Tuesday evening, after the original
OL,11,Fperformer fell ill.
OL,13,FFrench tenor Roberto Alagna, who was
OL,14,Fplaying Prince Calaf in a production
OL,15,Fof Giacomo Puccini's Turandot, became
OL,16,Funwell and could not go on stage for
OL,17,Fthe third act.
