OL,3,CRoyal Opera conductor replaces sick
OL,4,Ctenor during live show
OL,6,FThe Royal Opera's Head of Music
OL,7,FRichard Hetherington took his place,
OL,8,Fsinging from the wings, while the
OL,9,Fshow's choreologist Tatiana Novaes
OL,10,FCoelho covered his steps in costume.
OL,12,FAlthough the show resumed, the opera's
OL,13,Fmost famous aria, Nessun Dorma, was
OL,14,Fomitted. This left audience members
OL,15,Fdisappointed, with some reportedly
OL,16,Fbooing and leaving the auditorium.
OL,18,FThe performance also ended prematurely.
